WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.200
&gt;&gt;&gt; 
The Greyglers is a group of approximately

00:00:09.200 --> 00:00:15.089
200 Googlers, a little less than that, most
of us of a certain age.

00:00:15.089 --> 00:00:20.160
And this is our first big public event.
So thanks very much for coming.

00:00:20.160 --> 00:00:25.990
Just wanted to give you a really fast overview
of our primary goals.

00:00:25.990 --> 00:00:34.149
They are to raise awareness of age diversity
at Google and in our user base, to help attract

00:00:34.149 --> 00:00:42.420
experienced talent to Google, and to help
make Google culture and Google products and

00:00:42.420 --> 00:00:49.789
services welcome to people of all ages.
Anyone who can relate to our mission is welcome

00:00:49.789 --> 00:00:54.100
to join.
You don't have to have gray hair, or even

00:00:54.100 --> 00:00:57.699
gray roots, like some of us.
[ Laughter ]

00:00:57.699 --> 00:01:05.210
&gt;&gt;&gt; And today we're running a one-time special.
There's a goto address on the screen if you'd

00:01:05.210 --> 00:01:09.620
like to join.
It's goto/join-Greyglers.

00:01:09.620 --> 00:01:13.590
The first 50 people who join will get one
of these way-cool tee shirts.

00:01:13.590 --> 00:01:22.520
So don't forget to do that.
So we are honored that Vint is a Greygler,

00:01:22.520 --> 00:01:28.640
and he's also our executive advisor.
Speaking of the main attraction, Vint will

00:01:28.640 --> 00:01:33.080
be taking questions via Dory at the end of
his talk.

00:01:33.080 --> 00:01:37.250
So if you have questions, please be sure to
go and submit them.

00:01:37.250 --> 00:01:49.119
The address is up on the screen.
It's goto/Vinttalk -- one word -- hyphen questions.

00:01:49.119 --> 00:01:52.649
&gt;&gt;&gt; Hi.
As a Greygler, I can remember what things

00:01:52.649 --> 00:01:58.149
were like -- as a Greygler, I can remember
what things were like before the Internet

00:01:58.149 --> 00:02:01.939
existed.
Everybody had a lot of free time on their

00:02:01.939 --> 00:02:03.290
hands.
[ Laughter ]

00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:07.679
&gt;&gt;&gt; And no one had any information at their
fingertips.

00:02:07.679 --> 00:02:11.540
But Vint Cerf has done a lot to make that
change.

00:02:11.540 --> 00:02:19.069
With Bob Kahn, he invented the TCP/IP protocols
and the basic architecture that allow computers

00:02:19.069 --> 00:02:25.510
all over the world to link together and communicate.
And he spent most of his career providing

00:02:25.510 --> 00:02:32.510
leadership to develop the technology into
the Internet that we all know and love today.

00:02:32.510 --> 00:02:37.151
Because of his contributions, he is frequently
called one of the fathers of the Internet.

00:02:37.151 --> 00:02:45.090
And he has received quite a few awards of
recognition from lofty organizations.

00:02:45.090 --> 00:02:51.510
He received the Turing Award from the ACM.
He received the National Medal of Technology

00:02:51.510 --> 00:02:58.340
from President Clinton.
And, in a show of bipartisanship, he received

00:02:58.340 --> 00:03:03.069
the Medal of Freedom from President George
Bush.

00:03:03.069 --> 00:03:06.720
He's also --
[ Laughter ]

00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:15.470
&gt;&gt;&gt; He's also been designated one of the most
intriguing people of the year 1994 by "People

00:03:15.470 --> 00:03:17.810
Magazine."
[ Laughter ]

00:03:17.810 --> 00:03:27.060
&gt;&gt;&gt; So his talents span a broad spectrum.
He's been an advisor of many boards and organizations.

00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:32.849
He's received many, many awards, at least
two of which include the word "legend" in

00:03:32.849 --> 00:03:38.470
their title.
And he serves Google as our chief Internet

00:03:38.470 --> 00:03:41.200
evangelist.
So today he's going to share with us some

00:03:41.200 --> 00:03:47.629
of his insights into how the whole Internet
evolved and how we could have done it better

00:03:47.629 --> 00:03:59.070
if we had only had known these things in advance.
So with no further ado, here's Vint.

00:03:59.070 --> 00:04:04.930
[ Applause ]
&gt;&gt;Vint Cerf: You know, I always get nervous

00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:09.420
when people clap before you say anything.
It makes me want to just sit down, because

00:04:09.420 --> 00:04:12.319
it won't get any better than that.
[ Laughter ]

00:04:12.319 --> 00:04:18.690
&gt;&gt;Vint Cerf: I -- really, I'm stunned at this
overwhelming turnout.

00:04:18.690 --> 00:04:22.389
I do recognize, however, that theorem 208
might apply.

00:04:22.389 --> 00:04:27.110
It says, if you feed them, they will come.
I know there's food out there.

00:04:27.110 --> 00:04:31.350
So that's part of it.
The other thing I'm very conscious of.

00:04:31.350 --> 00:04:38.210
You probably have no idea how daunting it
is for me to confront a bunch of really smart

00:04:38.210 --> 00:04:40.660
Googlers.
I don't know how many of you know about the

00:04:40.660 --> 00:04:45.560
talking dog, some guy finds a dog that can
talk and he takes it around to various places.

00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:49.050
And everybody's all excited about the fact
