00:52:07.750 --> 00:52:10.490
next wave.
If you're interested in that, that's the product

00:52:10.490 --> 00:52:14.200
for you.
I mentioned earlier that there are sensored

00:52:14.200 --> 00:52:17.770
networks showing up on the Net.
Some of them are being driven by smart grid

00:52:17.770 --> 00:52:25.160
ideas, some are driven by being more thoughtful
about dealing with efficient use of energy.

00:52:25.160 --> 00:52:29.400
I have a sensored network at home.
And I'm proud to say it's a commercial thing.

00:52:29.400 --> 00:52:34.820
It's not me with a soldering gun.
It's from Arch Rock.

00:52:34.820 --> 00:52:39.901
It's running IPv6.
It's sampling temperature, humidity, and light

00:52:39.901 --> 00:52:42.221
levels in all the rooms of the house every
five minutes.

00:52:42.221 --> 00:52:45.460
And there is a server that's accumulating
that stuff.

00:52:45.460 --> 00:52:47.671
Now, one of the rooms in the house is the
wine cellar.

00:52:47.671 --> 00:52:52.730
And it's very important that the wine not
get up above 60 degrees Fahrenheit and the

00:52:52.730 --> 00:52:59.369
humidity not drop below about 50%.
That particular room is alarmed so that if

00:52:59.369 --> 00:53:03.890
the temperature is -- exceeds 60 degrees,
I get an SMS on my mobile.

00:53:03.890 --> 00:53:11.330
And it happened when I went to the -- a laboratory
 -- Argon National Laboratory.

00:53:11.330 --> 00:53:15.140
Just as I was walking in the door for a three-day
visit, my mobile goes off.

00:53:15.140 --> 00:53:20.640
It's the wine cellar calling.
"You've just breached the 60 Fahrenheit barrier."

00:53:20.640 --> 00:53:25.020
So every five minutes, I kept getting reminded
my wine was warming up.

00:53:25.020 --> 00:53:30.190
Unfortunately, my wife was away on some trip,
so she couldn't go and reset the cooler.

00:53:30.190 --> 00:53:34.750
So I called the guys at Arch Rock, and I said,
"Do you make actuators so I could do some

00:53:34.750 --> 00:53:37.599
remote actuation?"
They said, "Yes, that's a little project for

00:53:37.599 --> 00:53:41.830
the weekend."
I did think, though, that I could infer some

00:53:41.830 --> 00:53:44.140
things about what was going on when I wasn't
at home.

00:53:44.140 --> 00:53:46.970
For example, if somebody goes into the wine
cellar and turns on the lights, I might be

00:53:46.970 --> 00:53:50.310
able to detect that.
Of course, I don't know what they did in there.

00:53:50.310 --> 00:53:54.740
So the next step is to put RFID chips on all
